Package gov.nasa.worldwind.symbology

Provides classes for creating and displaying graphics from standard symbol sets.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IconRetriever
    Retrieves icons for symbols in a symbol set from a local disk or the network.
    SymbologyConstants
    Defines constants used by the World Wind symbology classes, including symbolic constants and modifier keys for MIL-STD-2525 tactical symbols and tactical graphics.
    TacticalCircle
    An interface for circular tactical graphics.
    TacticalGraphic
    TacticalGraphic provides a common interface for displaying a graphic from a symbology set.
    TacticalGraphicAttributes
    Holds attributes for a TacticalGraphic.
    TacticalGraphicFactory
    A factory to create TacticalGraphics.
    TacticalPoint
    An interface for tactical graphics that are positioned by a single point.
    TacticalQuad
    An interface for tactical graphics shaped like a quadrilaterals.
    TacticalRoute
    An interface for tactical graphics that depict routes: a series of point graphics connected by lines.
    TacticalSymbol
    TacticalSymbol provides a common interface for displaying tactical point symbols from symbology sets.
    TacticalSymbolAttributes
    Holds attributes for a TacticalSymbol.

    Basic implementation of the TacticalSymbolAttributes interface.
    TacticalGraphicLabel
    A label drawn as part of a tactical graphic.
    TacticalGraphicUtil
    Utility methods for working with tactical graphics.

Package gov.nasa.worldwind.symbology Description

Provides classes for creating and displaying graphics from standard symbol sets. See TacticalSymbol for information on tactical symbols (icons), and TacticalGraphic for information on other graphics.
